Text.Value: Why did you make me kill you?
What will happen to Boo without you?
Leave.
*The corpse remains silent. It does not know.*

EditorData.logicalname: DOESN'T KNOW ANSWER - DELETE IF NOT NEEDED

Text.Value: ...Boo! BOO!...
Jaheira... smarter than you... smarter... than Minsc...
How did your Harpers know to wait in ambush?
You were paying the Zhentarim? What for?
What did you want in the Counting House?
...Boo... BOO... BOO!...
Believed... in you... wrong...
Minsc... of... Rashemen...
*The corpse does not stir. It will answer no more questions.*
*The corpse regards you lifelessly.*
What is your real name, Stone Lord?
Zhentarim... precious... treasure...
*The spell's power wanes. You can ask no more questions.*
Kill... Nine-Fingers... seize... Guildhall...
Did you have anything of value worth taking?
*The corpse seems willing to speak - but not to its killer.*

Synopsis: Minsc's speak with dead dialogue. If you mention Boo, you will never get him off the topic - just nodes of him lamenting Boo in various states of vague dead grief and rage.
